what: fdacluster: Joint Clustering and Alignment of Functional Data — fdacluster-package
title: fdacluster: Joint Clustering and Alignment of Functional Data — fdacluster-package
text: Implementations k-means, hierarchical agglomerative DBSCAN clustering methods functional data allows jointly aligning clustering curves. supports functional data defined one-dimensional domains possibly evaluating multivariate codomains. supports functional data defined arrays also via 'fd' 'funData' classes functional data defined 'fda' 'funData' packages respectively. currently supports shift, dilation affine warping functions functional data defined real line uses SRSF framework handle boundary-preserving warping functional data defined specific interval. Main reference k-means algorithm: Sangalli L.M., Secchi P., Vantini S., Vitelli V. (2010) "k-mean alignment curve clustering" doi:10.1016/j.csda.2009.12.008 . Main reference SRSF framework: Tucker, J. D., Wu, W., & Srivastava, . (2013) "Generative models functional data using phase amplitude separation" doi:10.1016/j.csda.2012.12.001 .

code: lp(   direction = "min",   objective.in,   const.mat,   const.dir,   const.rhs,   transpose.constraints = TRUE,   int.vec,   presolve = 0,   compute.sens = 0,   binary.vec,   all.int = FALSE,   all.bin = FALSE,   scale = 196,   dense.const,   num.bin.solns = 1,   use.rw = FALSE,   timeout = 0L )

title: Linear and integer programming — lp
text: direction Character string giving direction optimization: "min" (default) "max." objective.Numeric vector coefficients objective function const.mat Matrix numeric constraint coefficients, one row  per constraint, one column per variable (unless transpose.constraints =  FALSE; see ). const.dir Vector character strings giving direction  constraint: value one "<," "<=," "=," "==," ">," ">=". (pair two values identical.) const.rhs Vector numeric values right-hand sides  constraints. transpose.constraints default constraint occupies row  const.mat, matrix needs transposed passed  optimizing code.  large constraint matrices may wiser  construct constraints matrix column--column. case set  transpose.constraints FALSE. int.vec Numeric vector giving indices variables  required integer. length vector therefore  number integer variables. presolve Numeric: presolve? Default 0 (); non-zero value means "yes." Currently ignored. compute.sens Numeric: compute sensitivity? Default 0 (); non-zero value means "yes." binary.vec Numeric vector like int.vec giving indices variables  required binary. .int Logical: variables integer? Default: FALSE. .bin Logical: variables binary? Default: FALSE. scale Integer: value lpSolve scaling. Details can found lpSolve documentation. Set 0 scaling. Default: 196 dense.const Three column dense constraint array. ignored const.mat supplied. Otherwise columns constraint number, column number, value; one row non-zero entry constraint matrix. num.bin.solns Integer: .bin=TRUE, user can request num.bin.solns optimal solutions returned. use.rw Logical: TRUE num.bin.solns > 1, write lp file read back solution first. just defeat bug somewhere. Although default FALSE, recommend set TRUE need num.bin.solns > 1, bug found. timeout Integer: timeout variable seconds, defaults 0L means limit set.

title: fdacluster 0.2.0
text: CRAN release: 2023-05-18 Add hierarchical clustering; Enforce n_clusters output via linear programming (LP) using lpSolve package; New caps class storing results functional Clustering Amplitude Phase Separation consistent way; Add tools comparing clustering results (mcaps objects, autoplot plot specialized method implementations); Add seeding strategies kmeans (via hierarchical clustering k-means++ k-means++ exhaustive search first center exhaustive search centers); Add within-cluster domain auto-extension via mean imputation; Add possibility cluster according phase variability instead amplitude variability. Renaming functions: perform k-means alignment, now use fdakmeans(), perform HAC alignment, now use fdahclust().
